	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				You do need skill in tailoring for this quest and a large sewing kit, unless <BR>
you ask some very nice tailor to sew the furs together for you.<BR>
The trivial for the first combination, of 4 patches of gnoll fur, is 21, so<BR>
your tailoring skill should be close to that.  When you combine the 4 patches of<BR>
gnoll fur you will get a gnoll fur patch. You then need to combine 4 gnoll fur <BR>
patches in your sewing kit to get a gnoll fur patch quarter. You then combine 4<BR>
gnoll fur patch quarters to get a gnoll fur bundle (AC 4, 5 sv vs cold, wt. 4, back slot)<BR>
You can wear this item as a cloak, or turn it in to the female rogue above the bank<BR>
to get a Fang of the wolf, Barbarian only piercing weapon. Magic item, 5dmg 26 dly<BR>
The trivial levels for all combinations other than with the patches of gnoll fur is <BR>
around 36.<BR>
Hope this helps 
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
